AP.title: Accepting party
AP.description: (3352) Party accepting goods, products, services etc.

AQ.title: Approved consignor
AQ.description: Person or company approved by the relevant authority in the country to pack and export specific goods under Customs supervision.

AR.title: Authorized exporter
AR.description: Exporter authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AS.title: Account servicing financial institution
AS.description: Identifies the financial institution servicing the account(s).

AT.title: Authorized importer
AT.description: Importer authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AU.title: Authorized trader (transit)
AU.description: Trader authorized/approved by Customs for special transit procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AV.title: Authorizing official
AV.description: Party that has delegated the authority to take a certain action on behalf of a company or agency.

AW.title: Applicant's bank
AW.description: (3234) Financial institution which is requested to issue the documentary credit.

A.title: Authenticating party
A.description: Party which certifies that a document is authentic.

AZ.title: Issuing bank
AZ.description: Financial institution which issues the documentary credit, if the applicant's bank is not acting as the issuing bank.

B1.title: Contact bank 1
B1.description: Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain aspects of the message.

B2.title: Contact bank 2
B2.description: Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain aspects of the message.

BA.title: Booking agent
BA.description: Party acting as a booking office for transport and forwarding services.

BB.title: Buyer's bank
BB.description: [3420] Bank employed by the buyer to make payment.

BC.title: Negotiating bank
BC.description: Financial institution to whom a negotiable documentary credit is directed.

BD.title: Documentary credit reimbursing bank
BD.description: A financial institution which reimburses documentary credit.

BE.title: Beneficiary
BE.description: The ultimate recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is reimbursed by the payor.

BF.title: Beneficiary's bank
BF.description: Identifies the account servicer for the beneficiary or the payee.

BG.title: Employer
BG.description: A party that keeps a person in service for payment.

BI.title: Buyer's financial institution
BI.description: Financial institution designated by buyer to make payment.

BJ.title: Release to party
BJ.description: Party to which the goods or container(s) is (are) to be released.

BM.title: Insured
BM.description: Party which is the object of an insurance contract.

BN.title: Insurance beneficiary
BN.description: Party which benefits from insurance coverage.

BO.title: Broker or sales office
BO.description: Party acting in the name of the seller as broker or as sales office.

BP.title: Building site purchaser
BP.description: Party at the building site responsible for the purchasing of goods and services for that particular site.

BQ.title: Cheque drawn bank
BQ.description: Identifies the bank on which the cheque should be drawn, as instructed by the ordering customer.

BS.title: Bill and ship to
BS.description: Party receiving goods and relevant invoice.

BT.title: Party to be billed for other than freight (bill to)
BT.description: Party receiving invoice excluding freight costs.

BU.title: Service bureau
BU.description: Party carrying out service bureau processing work, (e.g. a payroll bureau).

BV.title: Member
BV.description: Member of a group (e.g. of a group of persons or a service scheme).

BW.title: Borrower
BW.description: A person who acquires something temporarily with the promise or intention of returning.

B.title: Building site engineer
B.description: Party at the building site responsible for engineering matters for that particular site.

BY.title: Buyer
BY.description: Party to whom merchandise and/or service is sold.

BZ.title: Building site forwarder
BZ.description: Party at the building site responsible for forwarding the received goods on that particular site.

C1.title: In care of party no. 1
C1.description: A person taking responsibility on behalf of party no. 1.

C2.title: In care of party no. 2
C2.description: A person taking responsibility on behalf of party no. 2.

CA.title: Carrier
CA.description: (3126) Party undertaking or arranging transport of goods between named points.

CB.title: Customs broker
CB.description: Agent or representative or a professional Customs clearing agent who deals directly with Customs on behalf of the importer or exporter (CCC).

CC.title: Claimant
CC.description: Party who claims goods or insurance.

CE.title: Ceding company
CE.description: Company which cedes something to someone.

CF.title: Container operator/lessee
CF.description: Party to whom the possession of specified property (e.g. container) has been conveyed for a period of time in return for rental payments.

CG.title: Carrier's agent
CG.description: Party authorized to act for or on behalf of carrier.

CH.title: Connecting carrier
CH.description: Owner or operator of a transportation conveyance to which goods in a given transaction will be transferred.

CI.title: Commission processor
CI.description: Party who provides extra treatment to goods on commission base.

CJ.title: Previous member
CJ.description: Previous member of a group of persons or a service scheme.

CK.title: Empty equipment despatch party
CK.description: Party from whose premises empty equipment will be or has been despatched.

CL.title: Container location party
CL.description: Party from whose premises container will be or has been despatched.

CM.title: Customs
CM.description: Identification of customs authority relevant to the transaction or shipment.

CN.title: Consignee Cash pool top account servicing financial institution
CN.description: (3132) Party to which goods are consigned. Identification of a financial institution servicing the top account of a cash pool.

CNY.title: Cash pool level account servicing financial institution
CNY.description: Identification of a financial institution servicing the level account of a cash pool.

CNZ.title: Cash pool sub-account servicing financial institution
CNZ.description: Identification of a financial institution servicing the sub-account of a cash pool.

CO.title: Corporate office Freight payer on behalf of the consignee
CO.description: Identification of the Head Office within a company. Freight payer is a third party acting on behalf of the consignee.

COA.title: Entity in which a financial interest is held
COA.description: Business in which a financial interest is held.

COD.title: Quotation requesting party
COD.description: Party sending a request for a quotation.

COE.title: Party maintaining the codes used in the message
COE.description: The party which maintains the codes used in the message.

COF.title: Party maintaining the identifiers used in the message
COF.description: The party which maintains the identifiers used in the message.

COG.title: Dispatcher
COG.description: An individual responsible for sending something to a destination.

COH.title: Submitter of sample
COH.description: An entity responsible for the submission of a sample.

COJ.title: Primary health care provider
COJ.description: Health care provider that has primary responsibility for patient.

COL.title: Admitting health care provider
COL.description: Health care provider that admitted the patient.

COM.title: Referring health care provider
COM.description: Health care provider that referred patient to current provider of services.

CON.title: Supervising health care provider
CON.description: Health care provider that supervised the rendering of a service.

COO.title: Party providing financing
COO.description: Identifies the party providing the financing.

COP.title: Convoying party
COP.description: Party designated to escort the transported goods.

COS.title: Co-participant
COS.description: Identifies another party who participates in an activity.

COT.title: Involved party
COT.description: Party which is involved in an activity.

COV.title: Registered principal
COV.description: An individual who is registered as a principal for an entity.

COW.title: Freight payer on behalf of the consignor
COW.description: Freight payer is a third party acting on behalf of the consignor.

COY.title: Party responsible for disinfection
COY.description: Party responsible for performing disinfection operations.

COZ.title: Party responsible for refueling
COZ.description: Party responsible for performing refueling operations.

CP.title: Party to receive certificate of compliance
CP.description: Party acting for or on behalf of seller in matters concerning compliance.

CPA.title: Advising bank
CPA.description: Identifies the financial institution used by the issuing bank to advise the documentary credit.

CPB.title: Reimbursing bank
CPB.description: Identifies the financial institution through which the reimbursement is to be effected.

CPC.title: Advise through bank
CPC.description: Identifies the financial institution through which the advising bank is to advise.

CPD.title: Charges payer at destination
CPD.description: Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges concerning the destination operations.

CPE.title: Transport means master
CPE.description: [3408] Master of the means of transport.

CPF.title: Means of transport charterer
CPF.description: Charterer of the means of transport.

CPG.title: Excise party
CPG.description: Party to whom excise must be paid.

CPH.title: Copy report to
CPH.description: Party receiving a copy of a report.

CPI.title: Related healthcare party
CPI.description: A healthcare party related to the subject.

CPM.title: Patient discharged to
CPM.description: The party who receives the discharged patient.

CQ.title: Cheque order
CQ.description: Party to which the cheque will be ordered, when different from the beneficiary.

CR.title: Empty equipment return party
CR.description: Party to whose premises empty equipment will be or has been returned.

CS.title: Consolidator
CS.description: Party consolidating various consignments, payments etc.

CT.title: Consignee to be specified
CT.description: The party to be identified at a later time as the consignee.

CU.title: Container return company
CU.description: The company to which containers have to be returned.

CV.title: Consignee of vessel
CV.description: Party to which the vessel shall be delivered.

C.title: Consignee's agent
C.description: Party authorized to act on behalf of the consignee.

CY.title: Commissionable agent
CY.description: IATA cargo agent entitled to commission.

CZ.title: Consignor
CZ.description: (3336) Party which, by contract with a carrier, consigns or sends goods with the carrier, or has them conveyed by him. Synonym: shipper, sender.

DA.title: Available with bank (documentary credits)
DA.description: Financial institution with whom the documentary credit is available.

DB.title: Distributor branch
DB.description: The affiliate of a retailer or distributor.

DC.description: Party that splits up a large consignment composed of separate consignments of goods. The smaller consignments of goods were grouped together into that large consignment for carriage as a larger unit in order to obtain a reduced rate. Party to whom a refund is given.

DCP.title: Despatch charge payer
DCP.description: Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges concerning the despatch operations.

DCQ.title: Prescription database owner
DCQ.description: Organisation or person owning a prescription database.

DCR.title: Original prescriber
DCR.description: The doctor who issued the original prescription.

DCS.title: Temporary employee
DCS.description: A person employed on a temporary basis.

DCU.title: Quotation delivered to
DCU.description: Party to whom the quotation is to be or has been delivered.

DCY.title: Authorised issuer of prescription
DCY.description: Party authorised to issue a prescription.

DCZ.title: Authorised dispenser of medicine
DCZ.description: Organisation or person authorised to dispense medicine.

DD.title: Documentary credit account party's bank Imbalance settlement responsible party
DD.description: Bank of the documentary credit account party. A party that is responsible for settlement of the difference between planned and realised quantities.

DDA.title: Report responsible party
DDA.description: The party or person taking responsibility for a report.

DDB.title: Initial sender
DDB.description: The party who does the initial sending.

DDC.title: The party authorising the original prescription
DDC.description: The party authorising the issuer of the original prescription.

DDD.title: Applicant
DDD.description: A party who applies for something.

DDE.title: Meter reader
DDE.description: A party physically reading the meter.

DDF.title: Primary electronic business contact
DDF.description: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's primary contact for matters related to electronic business.

DDG.title: Alternate electronic business contact
DDG.description: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's alternate contact for matters related to electronic business.

DDH.title: Primary government business contact
DDH.description: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's primary contact for matters related to doing business with the government.

DDI.title: Alternate government business contact
DDI.description: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's alternate contact for matters related to doing business with the government.

DDJ.title: Past performance contact
DDJ.description: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's contact for matters related to the past performance of that entity.

DDK.title: Balance responsible party
DDK.description: A party responsible for balancing supply and consumption.

DDL.title: Group of passengers
DDL.description: A group of persons conveyed by a means of transport, other than the crew.

DDN.title: First financial institution in the transaction chain
DDN.description: Identifies the financial institution that is the point of entry into the interbank transaction chain.

DDO.title: Location manager
DDO.description: Party responsible for the management of the location.

DDP.title: Group leader
DDP.description: Party responsible for leading the group.

DDR.title: Consignor's freight forwarder
DDR.description: Identification of freight forwarder giving services to the consignor.

DDS.title: Consignee's freight forwarder
DDS.description: Identification of freight forwarder giving services to the consignee.

DDT.title: In transit crew member
DDT.description: The movement of a crew member from one country to another via the territory of an intermediate country for which no entry is intended.

DDU.title: In transit passenger
DDU.description: The movement of a passenger from one country to another via the territory of an intermediate country for which no entry is intended.

DDV.description: A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any imbalance between energy bought and consumed for all associated metering points.

DDW.title: Energy production imbalance responsible party
DDW.description: A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any imbalance between energy sold and produced for all associated metering points.

DDY.title: Transmission capacity allocator
DDY.description: A party managing the allocation of transmission capacity.

DDZ.title: Metering point administrator
DDZ.description: A party responsible for registering the technical specifications of metering points and the parties linked to them.

DE.title: Depositor
DE.description: Party depositing goods, financial payments or documents.

DEA.title: Metered data aggregator
DEA.description: A party responsible for aggregation of metered data.

DEB.title: Meter operator
DEB.description: A party responsible for the operation of a meter,  including installing  maintaining, testing, certifying and decommissioning.

DEC.title: Party connected to grid

DEE.title: Stowaway

DF.title: Documentary credit applicant

DG.title: Documentary credit beneficiary
DG.description: Party in whose favour the documentary credit is to be issued and the party that must comply with the credit's terms and conditions.

DH.title: Documentary credit account party
DH.description: Party which is responsible for the payment settlement of the documentary credit with the applicant's bank/issuing bank, if different from the documentary credit applicant.

DI.title: Documentary credit second beneficiary
DI.description: Party to whom the documentary credit can be transferred.

DJ.title: Party according to documentary credit transaction
DJ.description: Party related to documentary credit transaction.

DK.title: Documentary credit beneficiary's bank
DK.description: Financial institution with which the beneficiary of the documentary credit maintains an account.

DL.title: Factor
DL.description: Company offering a financial service whereby a firm sells or transfers title to its accounts receivable to the factoring company.

DM.title: Party to whom documents are to be presented
DM.description: Party to whom documents are to be presented.

DO.title: Document recipient
DO.description: (1370) Party which should receive a specified document.

DP.title: Delivery party
DP.description: (3144) Party to which goods should be delivered, if not identical with consignee.

DQ.title: Owner's agent
DQ.description: Person acting on delegation of powers of the owner.

DR.title: Driver
DR.description: Person who drives a means of transport.

DS.title: Distributor
DS.description: Party distributing goods, financial payments or documents.

DT.title: Declarant
DT.description: (3140) Party who makes a declaration to an official body or - where legally permitted - in whose name, or on whose behalf, a declaration to an official body is made.

DU.title: Owner's representative
DU.description: Person commissioned by the owner to represent him in certain circumstances.

DV.title: Project management office
DV.description: Party commissioned by the owner to follow through the execution of all works.

DW.title: Drawee
DW.description: Party on whom drafts must be drawn.

D.title: Engineer (construction)
D.description: Party representing the contractor to advise and supervise engineering aspects of the works.

DY.title: Engineer, resident (construction)
DY.description: Party commissioned by the owner to advise and supervise engineering aspects of the works.

DZ.title: Architect
DZ.description: A designer who prepares plans for buildings, ships, etc. and supervises their construction.

EB.title: Building inspectorate
EB.description: Party controlling the conformity of works to legal and regulation rules.

EE.title: Location of goods for customs examination before clearance
EE.description: The location where the goods are examined by customs before clearance.

EF.title: Project coordination office
EF.description: Party responsible for technical coordination of works.

EI.title: Controller, quality
EI.description: Party controlling the quality of goods and workmanship for the project.

EJ.title: Surveyor, quantity
EJ.description: Party responsible for the quantification and valuation of the works on behalf of the contractor.

EK.title: Surveyor (professional), quantity
EK.description: Party responsible to the owner for the quantification and valuation of the works.

EL.title: Project
EL.description: Party responsible for a project, e.g. a construction project.

EM.title: Party to receive electronic memo of invoice
EM.description: Party being informed about invoice issue (via EDI).

EN.title: Tenderer
EN.description: Firm answering an invitation to tender.

EP.title: Equipment drop-off party
EP.description: The party which drops off equipment.

EQ.title: Empty container responsible party
EQ.description: Party responsible for the empty container.

ER.title: Empty container return agent
ER.description: Party, designated by owner of containers, responsible for their collection as agreed between the owner and customer/ consignee.

ES.title: Contractor, lead
ES.description: Leader representing a grouping of co-contractors.

ET.title: Co-contractor
ET.description: Member of a grouping of co-contractors.

EU.title: Contractor, general
EU.description: Single contractor for the whole construction project, working by his own or with subcontractors.

EV.title: Subcontractor
EV.description: Firm carrying out a part of the works for a contractor.

E.title: Exporter
E.description: (3030) Party who makes - or on whose behalf a Customs clearing agent or other authorized person makes - an export declaration. This may include a manufacturer, seller or other person. Within a Customs union, consignor may have the same meaning as exporter.

EY.title: Subcontractor, nominated
EY.description: Subcontractor authorized by the owner after having been proposed.

EZ.title: Operator, essential services
EZ.description: Operator of essential services e.g. water, sewerage system, power.

FB.title: Nominated freight company
FB.description: Party nominated to act as transport company or carrier for the goods.

FC.title: Contractor, main
FC.description: Firm or grouping of co-contractors which has been awarded the contract.

FE.title: Credit rating agency
FE.description: A party which evaluates another party for credit rating.

FF.title: Factor, correspondent
FF.description: Factoring company engaged by another factoring company to assist the letter with the services provided to the clients (sellers).

FG.title: Buyer as officially registered
FG.description: Buying party as officially registered with government.

FH.title: Seller as officially registered
FH.description: Selling party as officially registered with government.

FI.title: Copy message to
FI.description: Party that is to receive a copy of a message.

FK.title: Previous Trade Union
FK.description: Employee organisation who previously represented an employee .

FL.title: Passenger
FL.description: A person conveyed by a means of transport, other than the crew.

FM.title: Crew member
FM.description: A person manning a means of transport.

FN.title: Tariff issuer
FN.description: The issuer of a tariff, e.g. a freight tariff.

FP.title: Freight/charges payer
FP.description: Party responsible for the payment of freight.

FQ.title: Container survey agent
FQ.description: The container survey agency that will survey the containers.

FR.title: Message from
FR.description: Party where the message comes from.

FS.title: Party authorized to make definite a contract action
FS.description: Party who has the authority to make definite a contract action.

FT.title: Party responsible for financial settlement
FT.description: (3450) Party responsible for either the transfer or repatriation of the funds relating to a transaction.

FU.title: Hazardous material office
FU.description: The office responsible for providing information regarding hazardous material.

FV.title: Party providing government furnished property
FV.description: The party responsible for providing government furnished property.

F.title: Current receiver
F.description: Current receiver of the goods in a multi-step transportation process (indirect flow) involving at least one grouping centre.

FY.title: Current sender
FY.description: Current sender of the goods in a multi-step transportation process (indirect flow) involving at least one grouping centre.

FZ.title: Grouping centre
FZ.description: A party in charge of groupage, including degroupage and regroupage.

GB.title: Chamber of commerce
GB.description: Name of the Chamber of Commerce of the town where the company is registered.

GC.title: Goods custodian
GC.description: (3024) Party responsible for the keeping of goods.

GD.title: Producer
GD.description: Party or person who has produced the produce.

GE.title: Registration tribunal
GE.description: Name of the tribunal where the company is registered.

GF.title: Slot charter party
GF.description: An identification code of a participant or user that books slots (space) on a ship, more likely on a long term basis on a series of sailings. He pays for the space whether he uses it or not.

GG.title: Warehouse
GG.description: The name of the warehouse where product is held. 1. This code value will be removed effective with directory D.06A.

GH.title: Applicant for job
GH.description: A person who applied for a job.

GL.title: Socially insured person
GL.description: A person who is registered in a social security scheme.

GM.title: Inventory controller
GM.description: To specifically identify the party in charge of inventory control.

GN.title: Processor
GN.description: Party or person who has or will apply a process.

GO.title: Goods owner
GO.description: The party which owns the goods.

GP.title: Packer
GP.description: Party or person who has undertaken or will undertake packing.

GQ.title: Slaughterer
GQ.description: Party or person who has undertaken or will undertake a slaughter.

GR.title: Goods releaser
GR.description: (3026) Party entitled to authorize release of goods from custodian.

GS.title: Consignor's representative
GS.description: Party authorised to represent the consignor.

GT.title: Rail carrier
GT.description: A carrier moving cargo, including containers, via rail.

GU.title: Originator of article number

GV.title: Procurement responsibility for order
GV.description: A code used to identify the organization which is responsible for the procurement.

GW.title: Party fulfilling all operations
GW.description: Code indicating the fact that the party identified carries out all operations within that company's activities.

GZ.title: Substitute supplier
GZ.description: Party which may be in a position to supply products or services should the main usual supplier be unable to do so.

HA.title: Party which delivers consignments to the terminal
HA.description: Party which delivers consignments to a terminal.

HC.title: Transit freight forwarder
HC.description: Freight forwarder to whom transit consignments are addressed, and from whom they are to be on-forwarded.

HD.title: Inspection and acceptance party
HD.description: The party who will perform inspection and acceptance.

HE.title: Transportation office
HE.description: The office that provides transportation information.

HF.title: Contract administration office
HF.description: The office responsible for the administration of a contract.

HH.title: Audit office
HH.description: The office responsible for conducting audits.

HJ.title: Foreign disclosure information office
HJ.description: The office that reviews sensitive information for foreign disclosure.

HK.title: Mark-for party
HK.description: The party within an organization for whom the material is marked to be delivered.

HL.title: Party to receive reports
HL.description: The party to whom reports are to be submitted.

HM.title: Alternative manufacturer
HM.description: Party identification of an alternative manufacturer for a product.

HN.title: Service performer
HN.description: The party who is performing a service.

HP.title: Final message recipient
HP.description: To identify the final recipient of the message.

HQ.title: Account owner
HQ.description: Identifies the owner of the account.

HR.title: Shipping line service
HR.description: Identifies the shipping line service organization.

HS.title: Creditor
HS.description: Party to whom payment is due.

HT.title: Clearing house
HT.description: Institution through which funds will be paid.

HU.title: Ordering bank
HU.description: Bank which instructed the sender to act on the transaction(s).

HV.title: Receiver of funds
HV.description: Identifies the financial party that receives the funds.

HW.title: Sender of funds
HW.description: Identifies the party that sends the funds.

H.title: Debtor
H.description: Party from whom payment is due.

HY.title: Presenting bank
HY.description: The bank which presents documents to the drawee.

I1.title: Intermediary bank 1
I1.description: A financial institution between the ordered bank and the beneficiary's bank.

I2.title: Intermediary bank 2
I2.description: A financial institution between the ordered bank and the beneficiary's bank.

IB.title: Intermediary/broker
IB.description: A person intervening between parties to produce agreement or reconciliation.

ID.title: Replacing manufacturer
ID.description: A code used to identify a party who replaces the previous party for the manufacture of an article.

IE.title: Non-resident third party company with whom financial account is held
IE.description: Identifies the non-resident third party company with whom the financial account is held.

IF.title: Non-resident group company with whom financial account is held
IF.description: Identifies the non-resident group company with whom the financial account is held.

IG.title: Non-resident beneficiary
IG.description: The ultimate non-resident recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is reimbursed by the payor.

IH.title: Resident beneficiary
IH.description: The ultimate resident recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is reimbursed by the payor.

IJ.title: Non-resident instructing party
IJ.description: Identifies the non-resident party originating the instruction.

IL.title: Resident instructing party
IL.description: Identifies the resident party originating the instruction.

IN.title: Insurer
IN.description: A person or company offering insurance policies for premiums.

IO.title: Insurance company
IO.description: A company engaged in the business of insurance.

IP.title: Insurance claim adjuster
IP.description: A party which adjusts losses on behalf of an insurer.

IQ.title: Domestic financial institution
IQ.description: Domestic party acting as financial institution.

IR.title: Non-domestic financial institution
IR.description: Non-domestic party acting as financial institution.

IS.title: Party to receive certified inspection report
IS.description: Party (at buyer) to receive certified inspection report.

IT.title: Installation on site
IT.description: A party who possesses the site on which an installation shall be made.

IU.title: Non-resident debtor
IU.description: Non-resident party who makes the payment or against whom a claim exists.

IV.title: Invoicee

IW.title: Non-resident creditor
IW.description: Non-resident party receiving the payment or against whom a liability exists.

I.title: Supplier work team

IY.title: Tenant manager

IZ.title: Party mandated to liquidate an enterprise

JA.title: Certified accountant
JA.description: Code identifying the party as a certified accountant.

JB.title: Goods collection party
JB.description: Party that will collect or has collected the goods.

JC.title: Party at final place of positioning
JC.description: Identifies the party at the final place of positioning.

JD.title: Customs office of clearance

PS.title: Packet switching
PS.description: The process of routing and transferring data by means of addressed packets so that a channel is occupied only during the transmission; upon completion of the transmission the channel is made available for the transfer of other packets (ISO).

SW.title: S.W.I.F.T.
SW.description: Communications address assigned by Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications s.c.

TT.title: Teletext
TT.description: Transmission of text/data via teletext. Communication service involving Teletypewriter machines connected by wire or electronic transmission media. Teletypewriter machines are the devices used to send and receive signals and produce hardcopy from them.

AA.title: Circuit switching
AA.description: A process that, on demand, connects two or more data terminal equipments and permits the exclusive use of a data circuit between them until the connection is released (ISO).

AB.title: SITA
AB.description: Communications number assigned by Societe Internationale de Telecommunications Aeronautiques (SITA).

AC.title: ARINC
AC.description: Communications number assigned by Aeronautical Radio Inc.

AD.title: AT&T mailbox
AD.description: AT&T mailbox identifier.

AF.title: U.S. Defense Switched Network
AF.description: The switched telecommunications network of the United States Department of Defense.

AG.title: U.S. federal telecommunications system
AG.description: The switched telecommunications network of the United States government.

AH.title: World Wide Web
AH.description: Data exchange via the World Wide Web.

AI.title: International calling country code
AI.description: Identifies that portion of an international telephone number representing the country code to be used when calling internationally.

AK.title: Videotex number
AK.description: Code that identifies the communications number for the online videotex service.

AM.title: International telephone direct line
AM.description: The international telephone direct line number.

AO.title: Uniform Resource Location (URL)
AO.description: Identification of the Uniform Resource Location (URL) Synonym: World wide web address.

CA.title: Cable address
CA.description: The communication number identifies a cable address.

EI.title: EDI transmission
EI.description: Number identifying the service and service user.

EM.title: Electronic mail
EM.description: Exchange of mail by electronic means.

F.title: Telefax X.400 address
F.description: Device used for transmitting and reproducing fixed graphic material (as printing) by means of signals over telephone lines or other electronic transmission media. The X.400 address.

GM.title: GEIS (General Electric Information Service) mailbox
GM.description: The communication number identifies a GEIS mailbox.

IE.title: IBM information exchange
IE.description: The communication number identifies an IBM IE mailbox.

PB.title: Postbox number
PB.description: The communication number identifies a postbox.

PS.title: Packet switching
PS.description: The process of routing and transferring data by means of addressed packets so that a channel is occupied only during the transmission; upon completion of the transmission the channel is made available for the transfer of other packets (ISO).

SW.title: S.W.I.F.T.
SW.description: Communications address assigned by Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications s.c.

TT.title: Teletext
TT.description: Transmission of text/data via teletext. Communication service involving Teletypewriter machines connected by wire or electronic transmission media. Teletypewriter machines are the devices used to send and receive signals and produce hardcopy from them.

G.title: Pager
G.description: Identifies that the communication number is for a pager.

I.title: National telephone direct line
I.description: The national telephone direct line number.

1.title: Place of terms of delivery
1.description: (3018) Point or port of departure, shipment or destination, as required under the applicable terms of delivery, e.g. Incoterms.

2.title: Payment place
2.description: [3108] Place where funds are to be, or have been made available to the creditor.

3.title: Tare check place
3.description: Place where equipment tare has been or must be checked for official assessment.

4.title: Goods receipt place
4.description: Place at which the goods have been received.

5.title: Place of departure
5.description: (3214) Port, airport or other location from which a means of transport or transport equipment is scheduled to depart or has departed.

6.title: Ward bed
6.description: A bed in a ward.

7.title: Place of delivery
7.description: (3246) Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

8.title: Place of destination
8.description: Port, airport or other location to which a means of transport or transport equipment is destined.

9.title: Place/port of loading
9.description: (3334 + 3230) Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are loaded on to the means of transport being used for their carriage.

10.title: Place of acceptance
10.description: (3348) Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier.

11.title: Place/port of discharge
11.description: (3392 + 3414) Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are unloaded from the means of transport having been used for their carriage.

12.title: Port of discharge
12.description: Port at which the goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

13.title: Place of transhipment
13.description: (3424) Place where goods are transferred from one means of transport to another (operational term).

14.title: Location of goods
14.description: [3384] Place where goods are located.

15.title: Place of transfer responsibility
15.description: Place where the responsibility is transferred.

16.title: Place of transfer of ownership
16.description: Place where the ownership of the goods is transferred.

17.title: Border crossing place
17.description: Place where goods are transported across a country border.

18.title: Warehouse
18.description: (3156) Warehouse where a particular consignment has been stored.

19.title: Factory/plant
19.description: Factory/plant relevant for a particular consignment.

20.title: Place of ultimate destination of goods
20.description: Place where goods will ultimately be delivered.

21.title: Terms of sale place
21.description: Place of departure, shipment or destination as specified in the terms of sale agreed between the parties.

22.title: Customs office of clearance
22.description: (3080) Place where Customs clearance procedure occur (CCC).

23.title: Port of release
23.description: Port where goods are released from Customs custody.

24.title: Port of entry
24.description: Port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

25.title: Country
25.description: Country relevant for a particular transaction.

26.title: City
26.description: City or town relevant for a particular transaction or consignment.

27.title: Country of origin
27.description: [3238] Country in which the goods have been produced or manufactured, according to criteria laid down for the purposes of application of the Customs tariff, of quantitative restrictions, or of any other measure related to trade.

28.title: Country of destination of goods
28.description: Country to which the goods are to be delivered.

29.title: Railway station
29.description: Name or identification of a railway station/yard relevant to a particular consignment.

30.title: Country of source
30.description: Country in which raw material or components were originally produced prior to manufacture or assembly in another country.

31.title: Building
31.description: A building or part thereof relevant to a particular consignment or transaction.

32.title: Beginning of chargeable section
32.description: First rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

33.title: Baseport of discharge
33.description: (3356) The port of discharge according to the tariff as opposed to the operational port of discharge. The goods may or may not be actually discharged at that port on the main transport.

34.title: Baseport of loading
34.description: (3322) The port of loading according to the tariff as opposed to the operational port of loading. The goods may or may not be actually loaded at that port on the main transport.

35.title: Country of exportation/despatch
35.description: (3220) Country from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Syn.: country whence consigned. Country of despatch: country from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

36.title: Country of ultimate destination
36.description: (3216) Country known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final country to which the goods are to be delivered.

37.title: Country of last consignment
37.description: [3331] Country where the goods are loaded onto the means of transport used for their importation.

38.title: Country of first destination
38.description: [3219] Country where the goods are offloaded from the means of transport used for their exportation.

39.title: Country of production
39.description: Country where item has been or will be produced.

40.title: Country of trading
40.description: Country where item has been or will be traded.

41.title: Customs office of entry
41.description: [3088] Customs office at which the goods enter the country of destination.

42.title: Customs office of exit
42.description: [3096] Customs office at which the goods leave the country of dispatch/export.

43.title: Place of Customs examination
43.description: Place where Customs undertakes a physical inspection of goods to satisfy themselves that the goods' nature, origin, condition, quantity and value are in accordance with the particulars furnished on the goods declaration (CCC).

44.title: Place of authentication of document
44.description: (3410) Place where document is signed or otherwise authenticated. Synonym: Place of issue of document.

45.title: Customs office of destination (transit)
45.description: (3086) Customs office at which a transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Customs office of transit termination.

46.title: Region of despatch
46.description: Region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

47.title: Region of destination
47.description: Region known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final region to which the goods are to be delivered.

48.title: Region of production
48.description: Region where item has been or will be produced.

49.title: Country of transit
49.description: Country through which goods transit.

50.title: Customs office of transit
50.description: [3106] Customs office which is competent for transit formalities en route.

51.title: Country of invalid transit guarantee
51.description: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is not valid.

52.title: Country of destination (transit)
52.description: Country at which a Customs transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Country of transit termination.

53.title: Charge and freight due from
53.description: Place or point from which charges and freight are charged.

54.title: Manufacturing department
54.description: A department within the manufacturing area (e.g. lacquering, assembly).

55.title: Charges and freight payable to
55.description: [3274] Name of place up to which freight charges and other charges are to be paid.

56.title: End of chargeable section
56.description: Last rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

57.title: Place of payment
57.description: Name of the location at which freight and charges for main transport are payable.

58.title: Full track loading or unloading
58.description: Identification of the station proceeding to the loading or unloading of a rail wagon on a full track site. (Used only when a rail station is obliged to transfer the load on another wagon for technical reasons - e.g. damage).

59.title: Place of loss
59.description: To identify the location where the loss occurred.

60.title: Place of arrival
60.description: Place at which the transport means arrives.

61.title: Next port of call
61.description: Next port which the vessel is going to call upon.

62.title: On-carriage port
62.description: Port of discharge at which the cargo is discharged from the vessel, used for transport after the main transport (transit port).

63.title: Sub-project location
63.description: A place at which works occur referring to a sub-project.

64.title: First optional place of discharge
64.description: The first optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

65.title: Final port or place of discharge
65.description: Name of the seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are finally (to be) unloaded from the means of transport used for their carriage according to the transport contract.

66.title: Express railway station
66.description: Railway station offering express transportation services.

67.title: Mixed cargo railway station
67.description: Railway station offering mixed cargo transportation services .

68.title: Second optional place of discharge
68.description: The second optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of shipper.

69.title: Next non-discharge port of call
69.description: A code to identify the next port of call for a vessel where no cargo will be discharged.

70.title: Third optional place of discharge
70.description: The third optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

71.title: Reconsolidation point
71.description: A place where cargo is reconsolidated.

72.title: Fourth optional place of discharge
72.description: The fourth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

73.title: Bill of lading release office
73.description: A location where bills of lading are released to customers.

74.title: Transhipment excluding this place
74.description: Place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is not authorised.

75.title: Transhipment limited to this place
75.description: Only place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is authorised.

76.title: Original port of loading
76.description: The port where the goods were first loaded on a vessel.

77.title: First port of call - non-discharging
77.description: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will not be discharging cargoes.

78.title: First port of call - discharging
78.description: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will be discharging cargoes.

79.title: Place/port of first entry
79.description: Place or port where final documentation is filed for Customs entry processing.

80.title: Place of despatch
80.description: Place at which the goods are taken over for carriage (operational term), if different from the transport contract place of acceptance (see: 10). Synonym: Place of origin of carriage.

81.title: Fifth optional place of discharge
81.description: The fifth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

82.title: Pre-carriage port
82.description: Port of loading at which the cargo is loaded on the pre- carriage vessel used for the transport prior to the main transport.

83.title: Place of delivery (by on carriage)
83.description: Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered.

84.title: Transport contract place of acceptance
84.description: Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier according to the contract of carriage.

85.title: Transport contract place of destination
85.description: Place to which the goods are destined.

86.title: Country of valid transit guarantee
86.description: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is valid.

87.title: Place/port of conveyance initial arrival
87.description: Place/port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the "Last place/port of call of conveyance" (125).

88.title: Place of receipt
88.description: Identification of the location at which the cargo is actually received.

90.title: Special treatment place
90.description: Place where one or more special treatments have happened or must happen.

91.title: Place of document issue
91.description: The place or location where a document is issued.

93.title: Station of application of additional costs
93.description: Rail station where, according to the transport contract, some chargeable operations must happen (re-weighting, re-fixing of the load, control on equipment and on consignment, etc.).

94.title: Previous port of call
94.description: Previous port which the vessel has called upon.

95.title: Sailing destination area
95.description: Geographical area to which the vessel's trip is destined.

96.title: Place of lodgement of documents
96.description: Customs station where, required documents for Customs declarations, have been lodged.

97.title: Optional place of discharge
97.description: The optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the bill of lading where cargo is discharged at the option of the shipper.

98.title: Place of empty equipment despatch
98.description: The location from which empty equipment is despatched.

99.title: Place of empty equipment return
99.description: The location to which empty equipment is returned.

100.title: Place/port of warehouse entry
100.description: Location (e.g. district) within a Customs territory where a warehouse entry was filed to enter merchandise into a Customs bonded warehouse.

101.title: Country of first sale
101.description: Name of country where firstly a sale took place.

102.title: Country of purchase
102.description: [3394] Country where the importer's co-contractor is domiciled or has his business.

103.title: Place of transfer
103.description: Place at which goods are transferred from one carrier to another (contractual term).

104.title: Place of deconsolidation
104.description: Place where a large consignment is de-grouped into smaller consignments.

105.title: Place of consumption
105.description: Place/location where goods enter the marketplace (commerce) of the importing country.

106.title: Region of origin
106.description: Region in which the goods have been produced or manufactured according to the criteria laid down for the purposes of the application of the Customs tariff, of quantitative restrictions or of any other measures related to trade (see: 3238).

107.title: Place of consolidation
107.description: Place where smaller consignments of goods are grouped together into a large consignment to be transported as a larger unit.

108.title: Rate combination point
108.description: Point over which sector rates are combined.

109.title: Place of prolongation decision of delivery delay
109.description: Place where it has been decided to prolong the delivery delay.

110.title: Recharging place/location
110.description: Place/location where a consignment has been changed of destination and is subject to a recharge note. (Complementary orders to modify the routing of the transport may be given, upon which a new charge calculation may be applied by the carrier).

111.title: Customs office of despatch
111.description: Customs office from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

112.title: Region of equipment availability
112.description: Region in which a piece of equipment is requested to be made available for on-hire.

113.title: Country of despatch
113.description: Country from which goods are despatched within a Customs union.

114.title: Customs office of export
114.description: Customs office from which goods are taken out of the Customs territory (CCC).

115.title: Free zone of export
115.description: Foreign free zone (desc: see 1131 = 131) from which goods are exported to the country of importation.

116.title: Region of export/despatch
116.description: Region from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Region of despatch: region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

117.title: Place of collection
117.description: Place where goods are to be or could be picked up (collected).

118.title: Customs office of departure
118.description: Customs office at which a Customs transit operation commences (CCC).

119.title: Customs office of transit guarantee
119.description: [3110] Customs office at which a security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is lodged.

120.title: Country of transhipment
120.description: Country where goods are transferred under Customs control from the importing means of transport to the exporting means of transport within the area of one Customs office which is the office of both importation and exportation (CCC).

121.title: Country of sale
121.description: [3116] Country where exporter's co-contractor is domiciled or has his business.

122.title: Customs office of destination
122.description: Customs office where the goods are to be cleared (CCC).

123.title: Wagon-load railway station
123.description: A railway station where rail wagons are loaded.

124.title: Siding
124.description: A short railway track for loading or unloading rail wagons, or bypassing of trains, connected with a main track by switch.

125.title: Last place/port of call of conveyance
125.description: Conveyance departed from this last foreign place/port of call to go to "Place/port of conveyance initial arrival" (87).

126.title: Country of previous Customs procedure
126.description: Country in which the Customs declaration for the previous Customs procedure has been lodged.

127.title: Customs office of registration of previous Customs declaration
127.description: Customs office where the previous Customs declaration has been lodged.

128.title: Participant sender location
128.description: Place where a participant in the movement of goods is located and can be contacted.

129.title: Wage negotiation district
129.description: The district to which workers belong for the purposes of union wage negotiation.

130.title: Place of ultimate destination of conveyance
130.description: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place to which a means of transport is ultimately destined.

131.title: Place of loading of empty equipment
131.description: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was loaded onto means of transport.

132.title: Place of discharge of empty equipment
132.description: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was unloaded from means of transport.

133.title: Region of delivery
133.description: (3246) Region to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

134.title: Petroleum warehouse
134.description: Bonded petroleum warehouse or the supplier source.

135.title: Place of entry (Customs)
135.description: Place at which the goods enter the Customs territory.

136.title: Living animals care place
136.description: Place where living animal cares are provided.

137.title: Re-icing place
137.description: Place where re-icing must be executed.

138.title: Weighting place
138.description: Place where weight can be ascertained.

139.title: Marshalling yard
139.description: Station where the wagons are disconnected and reconnected to form a new train.

140.title: Stopping station
140.description: Station where the train must stop or is stopped for unexpected handling.

141.title: Loading dock
141.description: Platform specially equipped for loading and unloading of rail wagons.

142.title: Port connection
142.description: Track connecting a rail station to a dock.

143.title: Place of expiry
143.description: Place where the documentary credit expires for presentation of required documents.

144.title: Place of negotiation
144.description: Place where the documentary credit is to be presented for negotiation.

145.title: Claims payable place
145.description: Place where insurance claims are payable.

146.title: Documentary credit available in
146.description: Place where the documentary credit is available with any bank.

147.title: Stowage location
147.description: [8042] Indication of the location on board a means of transport where specified goods or transport equipment have been or are to be placed.

148.title: For transportation to
148.description: Place/country where goods are to be transported to.

149.title: Loading on board/despatch/taking in charge at/from
149.description: Place/country where goods have to be loaded on board, despatched or taken in charge.

150.title: Container stack position
150.description: Stack position of a container at a terminal, depot or freight station.

151.title: Private box
151.description: A private box used for pick-up and delivery of packages, e.g. of express packages.

152.title: Next port of discharge
152.description: Next port at which goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

153.title: Port of call
153.description: Port where a vessel has called upon or will call upon.

154.title: Place/location of on-hire
154.description: Place/location where an object is contracted for use.

155.title: Place/location of off-hire
155.description: Place/location where an object's contract for use ends.

156.title: Other carriers terminal
156.description: A carrier terminal belonging to a carrier other than the original carrier.

157.title: Country of Value Added Tax (VAT) jurisdiction
157.description: The country governing the VAT regulation to which the transaction is subject.

158.title: Contact location
158.description: The site where a contact is located.

159.title: Additional internal destination
159.description: Any location within the consignee's premises where the goods are moved to.

160.title: Foreign port of call
160.description: A code to identify the foreign port where the vessel calls at or will call at.

161.title: Maintenance location
161.description: A location where maintenance has been or will be performed.

162.title: Place or location of sale
162.description: Place or location at which the sale takes place.

163.title: Direct investment country
163.description: Country in which a direct investment is made or withdrawn.

164.title: Berth
164.description: Location in port where the vessel is berthed or moored.

165.title: Construction country
165.description: Country in which the construction work is made.

166.title: Donation acting country
166.description: Country acting in the donation of aid.

167.title: Payment transaction country
167.description: Country of the foreign counterpart of the payment transaction.

168.title: Physical place of return of item
168.description: Physical place at which the item is returned, i.e. the location where the supplier receives the item form the customer.

169.title: Relay port
169.description: A location where cargo is transferred from one means of transport to another means of transport owned or operated by the same carrier under the same bill of lading.

170.title: Final port of discharge
170.description: Last port at which cargo is unloaded from a vessel before the cargo is moved to a place of delivery or destination.

171.title: Place of destination for pre-stacking prior to stowage
171.description: The destination location for which items are to be pre- stacked prior to being stowed together on a means of transport.

172.title: Reporting location
172.description: The location to which the information being reported is applicable.

173.title: Transport contract place of despatch
173.description: A place from which goods are despatched as per transport contract.

174.title: Place of residence
174.description: A place where a party lives.

175.title: Activity location
175.description: A place at which the activity occurs.

177.title: Construction site
177.description: A place at which construction works occur.

178.title: Place of embarkation
178.description: Place where the object is put, or goes, on board the conveyance.

179.title: Place of disembarkation
179.description: Place where the object or person disembarks from the conveyance.

180.title: Person birth place
180.description: [3486] Place where the person was born.

181.title: Registered office
181.description: Identifies the place or location of a registered office.

183.title: Place of business
183.description: Identifies the place or location of a business.

185.title: Location to send mail
185.description: Identifies the location to which mail is sent.

186.title: Foreign registration location
186.description: Identifies the place or location of foreign registration.

187.title: Tax filed from location
187.description: Identifies the location from which taxes are filed.

188.title: Filing location
188.description: Identifies the location of the filing entity.

189.title: Former location
189.description: Identifies an earlier or previous place or location.

190.title: Head office
190.description: Identifies the place or location of a head office.

191.title: Property
191.description: Identifies the place or location of property.

192.title: Correct location
192.description: Identifies the correct place or location.

193.title: Branch location
193.description: Identifies the place or location of a branch.

194.title: Former registered location
194.description: Identifies the former registered location of an entity.

195.title: Future location
195.description: Location to be used in the future.

197.title: Place of inquiry
197.description: Place to which an inquiry is made.

199.title: Country of last source
199.description: The country where a product or service was last sourced.

200.title: Place of handling
200.description: Place where a handling operation is to be, or has been, performed.

201.title: Country of origin as defined by transportation agency
201.description: Country of origin as defined by the transportation agency.

203.title: Sample location
203.description: Code identifying the location from which a sample is taken.

204.title: Hospital Advanced Dependency Unit (ADU)
204.description: A designated unit in a hospital for advanced dependency nursing care.

205.title: Hospital Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU)
205.description: A designated unit in a hospital for the provision of intensive care to neonates.

206.title: Hospital Paediatric Care Unit (PCU)
206.description: A designated unit in a hospital for the provision of care to paediatric patients.

207.title: Hospital Intensive Care Unit (ICU)
207.description: An intensive care unit in a hospital.

208.title: Hospital luxury room
208.description: A room in a hospital for patient accommodation of superior standard.

209.title: Hospital shared room
209.description: A room in a hospital for shared accommodation of patients.

210.title: Hospital private room
210.description: A room in a hospital for private accommodation of a patient.

211.title: Bidding area
211.description: An area for which bids can be made with the same price applicable to the whole area.

212.title: Price area
212.description: An area for which the same price is applicable to the whole area.

213.title: Country of destination of equipment
213.description: Country of the last place where the equipment will stop.

214.title: Aircraft airport stand
214.description: Code used to specify the airport stand allocated to the aircraft.

215.title: Airport passenger terminal
215.description: Code used to specify the airport terminal used for the embarking or disembarking of passengers.

216.title: Previous berth
216.description: Place or location in a port where a vessel was previously moored.

217.title: Next berth
217.description: Place or location in a port where a vessel will be moored, after moving from the current location.

218.title: Entity location
218.description: Identifies the place or location of the entity.

219.title: Goods depot
219.description: Depot where goods are received and are available for pick-up.

220.title: Disinfecting place
220.description: Place where disinfection has been or must be performed.

222.title: Place of live animal care
222.description: Place where live animal care has been or must be provided.

223.title: Phytosanitary control place
223.description: Place where phytosanitary control has been or must be performed.

224.title: Place for re-icing or de-icing

38.title: ACH savings corporate trade payment (CTP) debit

41.description: A credit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CCD+ payment format.

43.description: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CCD+ payment format.

46.description: A debit transfer via interbank means.

47.description: A debit transfer initiated through home-banking.

23.description: Amount of debit or credit note.

1.title: Project
