1.title: VAT, 1st value
1.description: First VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 1 to 3 different ways to set this value.

2.title: VAT, 2nd value
2.description: Second VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 2 or 3 different ways to set this value.

3.title: VAT, 3rd value
3.description: Third VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 3 different ways to set this value.

4.title: Additional royalties (Customs)
4.description: Royalties relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

5.title: Adjusted amount
5.description: The amount specified is the adjusted amount.

6.title: Amount reference currency
6.description: The owing amount in the currency used as reference in the transaction.

7.title: Agreed charge
7.description: Charges which parties agreed upon.

8.title: Allowance or charge amount
8.description: [5422] Total amount of allowance or charge.

9.title: Amount due/amount payable
9.description: Amount to be paid.

10.title: Amount in charge currency
10.description: Indicates that the amount is based on the charged currency.

11.title: Amount paid
11.description: Amount that has been paid.

12.title: Amount remitted
12.description: Amount which was remitted (see remittance advice).

13.title: Amount subject to total monetary discount
13.description: The amount is subject to a total monetary discount.

14.title: Amount target currency
14.description: The amount in the currency in which the amount is paid or has to be paid.

15.title: Average ledger balance
15.description: The addition of the balance all accounts divided by the number of accounts.

16.title: Bank release fee
16.description: The fee that a bank charges for releasing monies.

17.title: Batch total
17.description: The complete quantity of anything needed for or made in one operation or lot.

18.title: Brokerage
18.description: Fee charged by a broker for acting on behalf of a third party.

19.title: Buying commission
19.description: Commission paid by the importer to his/her agent for the service of representing him/her in the purchase.

20.title: Data value on carrier media (Customs)
20.description: Value of data contained on the carrier media (e.g. magnetic tape).

21.title: Cash discount
21.description: Cash discount given by the seller to the buyer.

22.title: Cash on delivery amount
22.description: [5017] Amount to be collected by carrier upon delivery of goods. This amount represents approximately the value of the goods.

23.title: Charge amount
23.description: The amount of money charged for the provision of a service or product.

24.title: Charge summary total
24.description: Code to indicate the total charges relating to a consignment.

25.title: Charge/allowance basis
25.description: The amount specified is the basis for calculation of charges/allowance.

26.title: Charges collect fee
26.description: The fee a party charges for collecting charges.

27.title: Charges in destination currency
27.description: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

28.title: Collect charge summary total
28.description: A summary total of collection charges.

29.title: Collect charges in destination currency
29.description: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

30.title: Collect freight charge including VAT
30.description: This is the total amount that has to be collected from the consignee or other intermediary intervening party - Including VAT-.

31.title: Collect freight charge without VAT
31.description: For legal accounting reasons the amount without VAT has to be announced, together with the amount of VAT.

32.title: Collect other charges due agent total
32.description: The total of other charges that are due to the agent.

33.title: Collect taxes total
33.description: The total amount of taxes to be collected.

34.title: Collected balance required
34.description: A certain sum of money that must be kept in an account.

35.title: Container cost
35.description: The cost of providing a container.

36.title: Converted amount
36.description: The amount is converted from another currency.

37.title: Credit on consignment
37.description: Credit deducted from the total invoice amount for the value of goods not included in a consignment but included in the invoice.

38.title: Invoice item amount
38.description: (5068) Total sum charged in respect of a single Invoice item in accordance with the terms of delivery.

39.title: Invoice total amount
39.description: [5444] Total sum charged in respect of one or more Invoices in accordance with the terms of delivery.

40.title: Customs value
40.description: [5032] Value declared for Customs purposes on those goods in a consignment which are subject to the same Customs procedure, and have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information and duty regime.

41.title: Assigned Customs value
41.description: Goods value assigned by Customs.

42.title: Total cash payments received by factor
42.description: Total allocated amount of cash payments received by a factor.

43.title: Declared total Customs value
43.description: [5070] Total value declared for Customs purposes of all goods in a consignment, whether or not they are subject to the same Customs procedure, or have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information, and duty regime.

44.title: Declared value for carriage
44.description: [5036] Value, declared by the shipper or his agent solely for the purpose of varying the carrier's level of liability from that provided in the contract of carriage, in case of loss or damage to goods or delayed delivery.

45.title: Deductible after importation charges (Customs)
45.description: Charges (e.g. construction, assembly, erection, maintenance or technical assistance) after importation, which are included in the total invoice price, that may be deducted to arrive at a Customs value.

46.title: Deductions (Customs)
46.description: [5020] Allowable deductions from the Customs value basis used.

47.title: Delivery fee
47.description: Fees incurred by delivery.

48.title: Deposit total
48.description: The whole amount of money that one entrusts for safekeeping.

49.title: Development necessary for production of imported goods (Customs)
49.description: Value of engineering, development, artwork, design work and plans and sketches carried out elsewhere than in the Customs territory and necessary for the production of the imported goods.

50.title: Disbursements
50.description: Amount of disbursements to be collected by the carrier according to the order given by the shipper.

51.title: Disbursements fee
51.description: Fee charged for the collection of disbursements.

52.title: Discount amount
52.description: (5014) The amount specified is the discount amount.

53.title: Discount amount due
53.description: The amount of discount that is due.

54.title: Distribution service fee
54.description: The fee charged for the provision of distribution services.

55.title: Duty amount
55.description: The amount of duty.

56.title: Duty/tax/fee basis amount
56.description: The amount specified is the basis for duty/tax or fee.

57.title: Equivalent amount
57.description: This amount is equivalent to the amount to be transferred, but in another currency.

58.title: Fee amount
58.description: The amount of a fee.

59.title: Fees paid year to date
59.description: Payments made for goods thus far.

60.title: Final (posted) amount
60.description: The amount posted to an account, finally, after charges/allowances.

61.title: Float (e.g. "cash float")
61.description: The status of funds in the process of collection.

62.title: Total payments on account received by a factor
62.description: Total unallocated amount of payments received by a factor.

63.title: FOB value
63.description: Identifies the value of the shipment free on board, named port of shipment (see FOB Incoterm of ICC).

64.title: Freight charge
64.description: Amount to be paid for moving goods, by whatever means, from one place to another, inclusive discounts, allowances, rebates, adjustment factors and additional cost relating to freight costs (UN/ECE Recommendation no 23).

65.title: Total indirect amount payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor
65.description: Total indirect amount of payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor.

66.title: Goods item total
66.description: Net price x quantity for the line item.

67.title: Insurance amount
67.description: Amount of insurance.

68.title: Insurance and transport charges (Customs)
68.description: (5488)+(5292) Sum total of transport and insurance charges (CCC).

69.title: Insurance and transport charges incurred outside Customs territory
69.description: (5488)+(5292) Insurance and transport charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

70.title: Insurance charges (Customs)
70.description: [5488] Amount of premium payable to the insurance company to insure the goods to the port or place of importation.

71.title: Insurance charges incurred outside of Customs territory
71.description: (5488) Insurance charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

72.title: Internal charges (Customs)
72.description: Charges incurred within a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

73.title: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account
73.description: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account.

74.title: Amount to be paid in advance
74.description: Amount which is to be paid before goods are delivered or the service is rendered.

75.title: Registered capital
75.description: Registered amount of equity of a company.

76.title: Investable balance
76.description: To put left over money in something offering profitable returns.

77.title: Invoice amount
77.description: [5068] Total sum charged in respect of a single Invoice in accordance with the terms of delivery.

78.title: Landing charges
78.description: The charges incurred in landing the goods into store in the country of importation, excluding Customs duties and taxes.

79.title: Total line items amount
79.description: The sum of all the line item amounts.

80.title: Licence fees related to imported goods (Customs)
80.description: Licence fees relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

81.title: Loading and handling cost
81.description: Cost incurred by loading and handling.

82.title: Lock box total
82.description: The complete amount of funds that customers mailed in to a specific location. Often times funds are sent to a post-office lock box in their city.

83.title: Lumpsum
83.description: An agreed sum of money, which is paid in full at one time. This term is often used in connection with charter parties.

84.title: Material consumed in production of imported goods (Customs)
84.description: Value of materials consumed in the production of the imported goods.

85.title: Maximum charge
85.description: The maximum amount that can be charged for a service or product.

86.title: Message total monetary amount
86.description: The total of all monetary amounts contained within the message.

87.title: Minimum charge
87.description: The minimum amount that can be charged for a service or product.

88.title: National preference basis amount
88.description: Amount giving the basis for national preference calculation.

89.title: Negative collected balance
89.description: Having a quantity of less than zero in an account.

90.title: Negative ledger balance
90.description: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a credit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a debit balance.

91.title: Net adjustment
91.description: The end-of-the-period total amount which is left after recording appropriate adjusting entries.

92.title: Net fee position
92.description: The payments left over after deductions or allowances have been made.

93.title: Net year to date excess (deficit)
93.description: A negative amount of an item.

94.title: No amount of insurance
94.description: No amount of insurance has been declared for a consignment.

95.title: No declared value for carriage
95.description: No value has been declared for purposes of carriage.

96.title: No declared value for Customs
96.description: No value has been declared for Customs purposes.

98.title: Original amount
98.description: Original amount, without charges, allowances or adjustment.

99.title: Other charges at destination
99.description: Code to indicate charges levied at destination.

100.title: Other charges due agent
100.description: Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to an agent.

101.title: Other charges due carrier
101.description: Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to a carrier.

102.title: Other commissions
102.description: Other commissions paid by the importer to his/her agent in relation to the goods being imported.

103.title: Other deductible charges
103.description: Other charges deducted from the total invoice value.

105.title: Other valuation charges (Customs)
105.description: Other valuation charges which are payable by reason of the importation or sale of the goods in the Customs territory.

106.title: Packing cost
106.description: Cost for packing concerning labour and/or material.

107.title: Packing cost (Customs)
107.description: [5448] Costs incurred for all containers and coverings of whatever nature which are considered as being one for Customs purposes with the goods, and the cost of packing whether for labour or material.

108.title: Parts incorporated in imported goods (Customs)
108.description: Materials, components, parts and similar items incorporated in the imported goods.

110.title: Pick-up fee
110.description: Fee incurring if item has been or will be picked up.

111.title: Positive collected balance
111.description: Having a quantity of greater than zero in an account.

112.title: Positive ledger balance
112.description: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a debit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a credit balance.

113.title: Prepaid amount
113.description: (5302) Amount which has been prepaid in advance.

116.title: Purchase amount
116.description: The cost of buying goods or services.

117.title: Quantity discount
117.description: Discount given for purchase of goods in bulk.

118.title: Quota value
118.description: The monetary value of a quota.

119.title: Received amount
119.description: The amount is what the bank received, and the one before charges/allowances.

120.title: Sales tax
120.description: Identifies the amount of sales tax payable.

121.title: Shipment value in domestic currency
121.description: The cost of transportation in domestic currency.

122.title: Specific amount payable
122.description: Amount that the consignor agrees to be invoiced or to pay. This amount is part of the total charges applied to the consignment.

123.title: Statistical value
123.description: [5218] Value declared for statistical purposes of those goods in a consignment which have the same statistical heading and country of origin.

124.title: Tax amount
124.description: Tax imposed by government or other official authority related to the weight/volume charge or valuation charge.

125.title: Taxable amount
125.description: Amount on which a tax has to be applied.

126.title: To collect
126.description: Amount that has to be collected.

127.title: Tools used in production of imported goods (Customs)
127.description: Tools, dies, moulds and similar items used in the production of the imported goods.

128.title: Total amount
128.description: The amount specified is the total amount.

129.title: Total amount subject to payment discount
129.description: Part of the invoice amount which is subject to payment discount.

130.title: Total charge due
130.description: Total amount of charges payable to the carrier.

131.title: Total charges/allowances
131.description: The amount specified is the total of all charges/allowances.

133.title: Total collect charges at destination
133.description: Total charges to be collected at destination.

134.title: Total declared
134.description: The total value of declared amounts.

135.title: Total freight due
135.description: Total amount of freight costs payable to the carrier.

136.title: Total invoice additional amount
136.description: (5140) Amount to be added to the sum of invoice line amounts to arrive at the total invoice amount.

137.title: Damage protection plan coverage
137.description: Indicates the amount of damage coverage provided under the Damage Protection Plan (DPP).

139.title: Total payment amount
139.description: A complete charge for goods or services rendered.

140.title: Total service charge
140.description: The complete payment owed to one who has performed work for another.

141.title: Cost, insurance and freight (CIF) value
141.description: Identifies the value of cost, insurance and freight. (Refer to ICC Incoterm CIF for an expanded definition).

142.title: Trade discount
142.description: Discount given to any purchaser at a particular commercial level e.g. at wholesale or retail level.

143.title: Transfer amount
143.description: The amount which has been transferred from buyer to the sellers bank.

144.title: Transport charges (Customs)
144.description: (5292) Cost incurred by shipper in moving goods, by whatever means, from one place to another under the terms of the contract of carriage, see UN/ECE Recommendation No 23. Synonym: freight charges (Customs).

145.title: Transport charges incurred outside Customs territory
145.description: (5292) Transport charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

146.title: Unit price
146.description: (5110) Reporting monetary amount is a "per unit" amount.

147.title: Acceptable quotation fluctuation amount
147.description: The maximum increase or decrease in constituent material fluctuation which will not result in an item price renegotiation.

148.title: Total payments under guarantee
148.description: Total amount paid under guarantee, such as under a factor's guarantee.

149.title: Valuation charge
149.description: A charge based on the value of goods or cargo.

150.title: Value added tax
150.description: [5490] Amount in national currency resulting from the application, at the appropriate rate, of value added tax (or similar tax) to the invoice amount subject to such tax.

151.title: Value insured
151.description: [5011] Representation in figures of the total sum covered by an insurance for a particular shipment.

152.title: Subsequent resale of imported goods (Customs)
152.description: Value of any part of the proceeds of any subsequent resale, disposal or use of the imported goods that accrues, directly or indirectly, to the seller.

153.title: Weight charge
153.description: A charge based on the weight of goods or cargo.

154.title: Amount to be collected
154.description: The monetary amount that is to be collected.

155.title: Standard duty
155.description: Standard Customs duty that would apply if special provisions did not apply.

156.title: G-Amount
156.description: Amount out of total invoice amount being paid into a blocked account.

157.title: Insurance value
157.description: (5010) Value for which the goods are insured.

158.title: Insurance and transport charges incurred inside Customs territory
158.description: (5488)+(5292) Charges to be paid for moving goods, by whatever means, from the point of entry into the Customs territory (within a Customs union: to the point of entry in the final destination country).

159.title: Licence (value deducted)
159.description: Amount in the currency of the licence to be written off from the total licence value.

160.title: Other costs
160.description: (5346) Costs, other than packing, freight and insurance costs, specified separately.

161.title: Duty, tax or fee amount
161.description: Amount of duty, tax or fee.

162.title: Customs duty paid
162.description: Amount which can be deducted from the stated invoice price where that price includes the Customs duty amount.

163.title: Wage tax share
163.description: Wage tax share of total amount to be paid directly to tax collector.

164.title: Social securities premiums share
164.description: Social securities share of total amount to be paid directly to the social securities collector.

165.title: Adjustment amount
165.description: Amount being the balance of the amount to be adjusted and the adjusted amount.

166.title: Guarantee amount (Customs)
166.description: Amount of the guarantee placed with Customs.

167.title: Actual versus calculated price difference
167.description: Difference between actual and calculated price.

168.title: Tax sub-totals
168.description: A sub total of tax values.

169.title: Alternate currency total amount
169.description: The total amount as expressed in an alternate currency.

170.title: Document amount
170.description: The monetary value stated within a related document.

171.title: Total reassignments of factored invoices
171.description: Total amount of factored invoices and credit notes reassigned to the seller or to another factor.

172.title: Stated amount
172.description: The monetary amount that has been declared.

174.title: Balance brought forward
174.description: Opening balance of the account brought forward from the prior accounting period.

175.title: Message total additional amount
175.description: An amount in addition to the total message value.

177.title: Message total amount prepaid
177.description: Total of all prepaid amounts within the message.

182.title: Any other specification/tolerance
182.description: Any further qualification of the amount.

489.title: Total allowances, not included in transaction amount
489.description: Total allowances which are not included in the transaction amount.

490.title: Late delivery penalty
490.description: Amount to be paid in case of late delivery.

491.title: Debt financing charge
491.description: A charge amount related to the financing of a debt.

492.title: Debt financing allowance
492.description: An allowance amount related to the financing of a debt.

493.title: Cancellation charge
493.description: The amount charged because of a cancellation.

494.title: Incurred cost
494.description: The amount which has been incurred.

496.title: Total returnable packaging deposit amount
496.description: Total deposit amount for returnable packaging.

497.title: Goods and services total amount excluding returnable goods deposits
497.description: Total amount of goods and services excluding deposits for returnable goods.

498.title: Waiting time indemnity amount
498.description: The monetary amount which is used as an indemnity for waiting.

499.title: Total net amount excluding Value Added Tax (VAT)
499.description: The total net monetary amount excluding Value Added Tax (VAT).

500.title: Interest on late payment of solidarity fund contribution
500.description: Interest to pay because payment date of contribution solidarity fund was exceeded.

501.title: Interest on late payment of employee's additional contribution to solidarity fund
501.description: Interest to pay because payment date of employee's additional contribution is exceeded.

502.title: Taxable disbursement amount
502.description: Amount of disbursement on which tax must be applied.

504.title: Daily contribution
504.description: Amount paid on a daily basis.

505.title: Rental amount
505.description: The amount to be paid for the right to use a place, product or service.

506.title: Gross progress payment amount
506.description: Gross monetary amount paid or to be paid at intervals.

507.title: Net progress payment amount
507.description: Net monetary amount paid or to be paid at intervals.

508.title: Value of returned product
508.description: Value of product returned by the customer.

509.title: Unit allowance amount
509.description: The monetary amount of an allowance for each unit.

510.title: Remaining available overdraft
510.description: The amount still available within the limit of the overdraft.

511.title: Unit charge amount
511.description: The monetary amount of a charge for each unit.

512.title: Agreed monetary amount credit line limit
512.description: Limit of the agreed monetary amount credit line.

514.title: Amount for pre-advising
514.description: The amount is for pre-advising only.

515.title: Supplement
515.description: The monetary amount represents the price of extra cost to pay in addition to the normal price.

516.title: Debit balance at closing date of accounting period under review
516.description: The monetary amonunt is the debit balance at the closing date of the accounting period under review.

517.title: Credit balance at closing date of accounting period under review
517.description: The monetary amount is the credit balance at the closing date of the accounting period under review.

518.title: Debit balance at starting date of accounting period under review
518.description: The monetary amount is the debit balance at the starting date of the accounting period under review.

519.title: Credit balance at starting date of accounting period under review
519.description: The monetary amount is the credit balance at the starting date of the accounting period under review.

520.title: Total of debit balances at closing date of accounting period under review
520.description: The monetary amount is the total of debit balances at the closing date of the accounting period under review.

521.title: Total of credit balances at closing date of accounting period under review
521.description: The monetary amount is the total of credit balances at the closing date of the accounting period under review.

522.title: Total of debit balances at starting date of accounting period under review
522.description: The monetary amount is the total of debit balances at the starting date of the accounting period under review.

523.title: Total of credit balances at starting date of accounting period under review
523.description: The monetary amount is the total of credit balances at the starting date of the accounting period under review.

524.title: Cost accounting entry amount
524.description: Code identifying the amount of a cost accounting entry.

525.title: Tariff
525.description: The monetary amount represents the tariff.

526.title: Volume discount
526.description: A discount for reaching or exceeding an agreed volume.

527.title: Product range discount
527.description: Discount for the purchase of a whole range of products.

528.title: Calculation basis excluding all taxes
528.description: The amount used as the basis for calculation excludes all taxes.

529.title: Calculation basis which includes all taxes except VAT
529.description: The amount, used as the basis for calculation, which includes all taxes except Value Added Tax (VAT).

531.title: Total returnable packaging rental amount
531.description: Total rental amount for returnable packaging.

ZZZ.title: Mutually defined
ZZZ.description: Mutually defined monetary amount.

1.title: Definition
1.description: To define the index.

2.title: Contents
2.description: To record the contents of the index.

1.title: Percentage
1.description: The index value is represented in a proportion.

1.title: Normal
1.description: As normally agreed between parties.

2.title: Special
2.description: A contribution not usually made.

3.title: Reversal
3.description: Reversing a previous contribution.

4.title: Back payment
4.description: Payment is a period prior to the normal period.

5.title: Advanced payment
5.description: Payment is for a period post the normal period.

6.title: Ceasing contributions
6.description: Payment is irregular as contributions ceased from the specified date.

ZZZ.title: Mutually defined
ZZZ.description: Mutually defined contribution qualifier.

1.title: Company
1.description: Company payment.

2.title: Company award
2.description: Company payment as per an industry or similar industrial award agreement.

3.title: Company over-award
3.description: Company payment which is higher than an industry or similar award agreement.

4.title: Lump sum
4.description: Payment is in the form of a single payment.

5.title: Company additional
5.description: Additional company payment.

6.title: Company voluntary
6.description: A company payment which is paid on a voluntary basis.

7.title: Member voluntary
7.description: A member payment which is paid on a voluntary basis.

8.title: Member additional
8.description: Additional member payment.

9.title: Member individual
9.description: Single payment by an individual member.

10.title: Group
10.description: Payment as part of a group plan or scheme.

11.title: Other
11.description: Contribution type differs from any of the other coded values.

ZZZ.title: Mutually defined
ZZZ.description: Mutually defined contribution type.

AAA.title: Calculation net
AAA.description: The price stated is the net price including allowances/ charges. Allowances/charges may be stated for information only.

AAB.title: Calculation gross
AAB.description: The price stated is the gross price to which allowances/ charges must be applied.

AAC.title: Allowances and charges not included, tax included
AAC.description: The price does not include the allowances and charges, but includes the taxes.

AAD.title: Average selling price
AAD.description: Average selling price of a product.

AAE.title: Information price, excluding allowances or charges, including taxes
AAE.description: The price stated is for information purposes only and excludes all allowances and charges. Taxes however are included in the price.

AAF.title: Information price, excluding allowances or charges, and taxes
AAF.description: The price stated is for information purposes only and excludes all allowances, charges and taxes.

AAG.title: Additive unit price component
AAG.description: A code to indicate that the price described is an additive component of the total price.

CAL.title: Calculation price
CAL.description: The price stated is the price for the calculation of the line item amount.

INF.title: Information
INF.description: The price is provided for information.

INV.title: Invoice price
INV.description: Referenced price taken from an invoice.

ZZZ.title: Mutually defined
ZZZ.description: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

AAA.title: Petroleum tax
AAA.description: A tax levied on the volume of petroleum being transacted.

AAB.title: Provisional countervailing duty cash
AAB.description: Countervailing duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of subsidization by Customs.

AAC.title: Provisional countervailing duty bond
AAC.description: Countervailing duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on subsidization by Customs.

AAD.title: Tobacco tax
AAD.description: A tax levied on tobacco products.

AAE.title: Energy fee
AAE.description: General fee or tax for the use of energy.

AAF.title: Coffee tax
AAF.description: A tax levied specifically on coffee products.

AAG.title: Harmonised sales tax, Canadian
AAG.description: A harmonized sales tax consisting of a goods and service tax, a Canadian provincial sales tax and, as applicable, a Quebec sales tax which is recoverable.

AAH.title: Quebec sales tax
AAH.description: A sales tax charged within the Canadian province of Quebec which is recoverable.

AAI.title: Canadian provincial sales tax
AAI.description: A sales tax charged within Canadian provinces which is non-recoverable.

AAJ.title: Tax on replacement part
AAJ.description: A tax levied on a replacement part, where the original part is returned.

ADD.title: Anti-dumping duty
ADD.description: Duty applied to goods ruled to have been dumped in an import market at a price lower than that in the exporter's domestic market.

BOL.title: Stamp duty (Imposta di Bollo)
BOL.description: Tax required in Italy, which may be fixed or graduated in various circumstances (e.g. VAT exempt documents or bank receipts).

CAP.title: Agricultural levy
CAP.description: Levy imposed on agricultural products where there is a difference between the selling price between trading countries.

CAR.title: Car tax
CAR.description: A tax that is levied on the value of the automobile.

CST.title: Commodity specific tax
CST.description: Tax related to a specified commodity, e.g. illuminants, salts.

CUD.title: Customs duty
CUD.description: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory (CCC).

CVD.title: Countervailing duty
CVD.description: A duty on imported goods applied for compensate for subsidies granted to those goods in the exporting country.

ENV.title: Environmental tax
ENV.description: Tax assessed for funding or assuring environmental protection or clean-up.

EC.title: Excise duty
EC.description: Customs or fiscal authorities code to identify a specific or ad valorem levy on a specific commodity, applied either domestically or at time of importation.

EP.title: Agricultural export rebate
EP.description: Monetary rebate given to the seller in certain circumstances when agricultural products are exported.

FET.title: Federal excise tax
FET.description: Tax levied by the federal government on the manufacture of specific items.

GST.title: Goods and services tax
GST.description: Tax levied on the final consumption of goods and services throughout the production and distribution chain.

IND.title: Individual tax
IND.description: A tax levied based on an individual's ability to pay.

LAC.title: Business license fee
LAC.description: Government assessed charge for permit to do business.

LDP.title: Light dues payable
LDP.description: Fee levied on a vessel to pay for port navigation lights.

LOC.title: Local sales tax
LOC.description: Assessment charges on sale of goods or services by city, borough country or other taxing authorities below state or provincial level.

LST.title: Lust tax
LST.description: Tax imposed for clean-up of leaky underground storage tanks.

MCA.title: Monetary compensatory amount
MCA.description: Levy on Common Agricultural Policy (European Union) goods used to compensate for fluctuating currencies between member states.

MCD.title: Miscellaneous cash deposit
MCD.description: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a final decision being made on any aspect related to imported goods (except valuation) by Customs.

PDB.title: Provisional duty bond
PDB.description: Anti-dumping duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on dumping by Customs.

PDC.title: Provisional duty cash
PDC.description: Anti-dumping duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of dumping by Customs.

PRF.title: Preference duty
PRF.description: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory falling under a preferential regime such as Generalised System of Preferences (GSP).

SSS.title: Shifted social securities
SSS.description: Social securities share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the social securities collector.

STT.title: State/provincial sales tax
STT.description: All applicable sale taxes by authorities at the state or provincial level, below national level.

SUP.title: Suspended duty
SUP.description: Duty suspended or deferred from payment.

SUR.title: Surtax
SUR.description: A tax or duty applied on and in addition to existing duties and taxes.

SWT.title: Shifted wage tax
SWT.description: Wage tax share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the tax collector(s office).

TAC.title: Alcohol mark tax
TAC.description: A tax levied based on the type of alcohol being obtained.

TOT.title: Total
TOT.description: The summary amount of all taxes.

TO.title: Turnover tax
TO.description: Tax levied on the total sales/turnover of a corporation.

TTA.title: Tonnage taxes
TTA.description: Tax levied based on the vessel's net tonnage.

VAD.title: Valuation deposit
VAD.description: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on valuation of the goods being made.

VAT.title: Value added tax
VAT.description: A tax on domestic or imported goods applied to the value added at each stage in the production/distribution cycle.

1.title: Handling commission
1.description: Fee for the processing of documentary credit, collection and payment which are charged to the customer.

2.title: Amendment commission
2.description: Fee for amendments in documentary credit and collection business (not extensions and increases of documentary credits).

3.title: Acceptance commission
3.description: Fee for the acceptance of draft in documentary credit and collection business which are drawn on us (also to be seen as a kind of 'guarantee commission').

4.title: Commission for obtaining acceptance
4.description: Fee for obtaining an acceptance under collections on the basis of 'documents against acceptance'.

5.title: Commission on delivery
5.description: Fee for delivery of documents without corresponding payment.

6.title: Advising commission
6.description: Fee for advising documentary credits (charged also in case of confirmed credits).

7.title: Confirmation commission
7.description: Fee for confirmation of credit.

8.title: Deferred payment commission
8.description: Fee for the deferred payment period under documentary credits confirmed by bank. This fee are charges for the period from presentation of the document until due date of payment.

9.title: Commission for taking up documents
9.description: Fee charged to the foreign bank for the processing of documentary credit.

10.title: Opening commission
10.description: Fee for opening revocable documentary credit.

11.title: Fee for payment under reserve
11.description: Fee charged to the customer for discrepancies in credit documents in the case of which the bank have to stipulate payment under reserve.

12.title: Discrepancy fee
12.description: Fee charged to the foreign bank for discrepancies in credit documents.

13.title: Domicilation commission
13.description: Fee for the domicilation of bills with the bank.

14.title: Commission for release of goods
14.description: Commission for the release of goods sent to the bank.

15.title: Collection commission
15.description: Fee for settling collections on the basis of 'documents against payments'.

16.title: Negotiation commission
16.description: Fee for the purchase of documents under sight credit for the first ten days.

17.title: Return commission
17.description: Fee for cheques, bills and collections returned unpaid and/or recalled.

18.title: B/L splitting charges
18.description: Fee for the splitting of bills of lading.

19.title: Trust commission
19.description: Fee for the handling on a fiduciary basis of imported goods that have been warehoused.

20.title: Transfer commission
20.description: Fee for the transfer of transferable documentary credits.

21.title: Commission for opening irrevocable documentary credits
21.description: Fee for opening irrevocable documentary credits. This fee is a kind of 'Guarantee commission' as compensation for the commitment into which the bank have entered on the customers behalf; similar to confirmation commission, acceptance commission.

22.title: Pre-advice commission
22.description: Fee for the pre-advice of a documentary credit.

23.title: Supervisory commission
23.description: Fee for the supervising unconfirmed documentary credits with a deferred payment period.

24.title: Model charges
24.description: Fee for decoding telex messages.

25.title: Risk commission
25.description: Commission in addition to the confirmation commission for documentary credits from sensitive countries.

26.title: Guarantee commission
26.description: Commission for drawing up guaranties.

27.title: Reimbursement commission
27.description: Fee for reimbursement of, for example, documentary credits.

28.title: Stamp duty
28.description: Tax payable on bills in accordance with national bill of exchange legislation.

29.title: Brokerage
29.description: Brokers commission arising, in trade with foreign currencies.

30.title: Bank charges
30.description: Charges deducted/claimed by other banks involved in the transaction.

31.title: Bank charges information
31.description: Charges not included in the total charge amount i.e. the charges are for information only.

32.title: Courier fee
32.description: Fee for use of courier service.

33.title: Phone fee
33.description: Fee for use of phone.

34.title: Postage fee
34.description: Fee for postage.

35.title: S.W.I.F.T. fee
35.description: Fee for use of S.W.I.F.T.

36.title: Telex fee
36.description: Fee for telex.

37.title: Penalty for late delivery of documents
37.description: Penalty imposed when documents are delivered late.

38.title: Penalty for late delivery of valuation of works
38.description: Penalty imposed when valuation of works is delivered late.

39.title: Penalty for execution of works behind schedule
39.description: Penalty imposed when the execution of works is behind schedule.

40.title: Other penalties
40.description: Penalty imposed for other reasons.

41.title: Bonus for works ahead of schedule
41.description: Bonus for completing work ahead of schedule.

42.title: Other bonus
42.description: Bonus earned for other reasons.

43.title: Penalty refund
43.description: Self explanatory. 1. This code value will be removed effective with directory D.05A.

44.title: Project management cost
44.description: Cost for project management.

45.title: Pro rata retention
45.description: Proportional retention charge.

46.title: Contractual retention
46.description: Contractual retention charge.

47.title: Other retentions
47.description: Retention charge not otherwise specified.

48.title: Interest on arrears
48.description: Interest for late payment.

49.title: Interest
49.description: Cost of using money.

50.title: Charge per credit cover
50.description: Unit charge per credit cover established.

51.title: Charge per unused credit cover
51.description: Unit charge per unused credit cover.

52.title: Minimum commission
52.description: Minimum commission charge.

53.title: Factoring commission
53.description: Commission charged for factoring services.

54.title: Chamber of commerce charge
54.description: Identifies the charges from the chamber of commerce.

55.title: Transfer charges
55.description: Charges for transfer.

56.title: Repatriation charges
56.description: Charges for repatriation.

57.title: Miscellaneous charges
57.description: Not specifically defined charges.

58.title: Foreign exchange charges
58.description: Charges for foreign exchange.

59.title: Agreed debit interest charge
59.description: Charge for agreed debit interest

60.title: Manufacturer's consumer discount
60.description: A discount given by the manufacturer which should be passed on to the consumer.

61.title: Fax advice charge
61.description: Charge for fax advice.

62.title: Due to military status
62.description: Allowance granted because of the military status.

63.title: Due to work accident
63.description: Allowance granted to a victim of a work accident.

64.title: Special agreement
64.description: An allowance or charge as specified in a special agreement.

65.title: Production error discount
65.description: A discount given for the purchase of a product with a production error.

66.title: New outlet discount
66.description: A discount given at the occasion of the opening of a new outlet.

67.title: Sample discount
67.description: A discount given for the purchase of a sample of a product.

68.title: End-of-range discount
68.description: A discount given for the purchase of an end-of-range product.

69.title: Charge for a customer specific finish
69.description: A charge for the addition of a customer specific finish to a product.

70.title: Incoterm discount
70.description: A discount given for a specified Incoterm.

71.title: Point of sales threshold allowance
71.description: Allowance for reaching or exceeding an agreed sales threshold at the point of sales.

A.title: Added to the baseline item unit price
A.description: Price is to be added to the base line unit price.

I.title: Included in the baseline item unit price
I.description: Price is included in the base line unit price.

S.title: Subtracted from the baseline item unit price
S.description: Price is to be subtracted from the base line unit price.

1.title: All charges
1.description: All amounts calculated by the carrier in accordance with tariffs or in case of special events during the voyage (e.g. Rail - freights costs - additional costs).

2.title: Additional charges
2.description: Charges calculated by the carrier for specific events like re-weighting, re-loading, unexpected operations, services required during the voyage, etc.

3.title: Transport charges + additional charges
3.description: Transport charges plus Additional charges (e.g. for re- loading, re-weighting or unexpected operations) that must be precised in the payment conditions by the consignor (other charges must be taken in account by the consignee).

4.title: Basic freight
4.description: The basic freight payable on the cargo as per tariff.

5.title: Destination haulage charges
5.description: Haulage charges for transporting goods to the destination.

6.title: Disbursement
6.description: Sums paid out by ship's agent at a port and recovered from the carrier.

7.title: Destination port charges
7.description: Charges payable at the port of destination.

8.title: Miscellaneous charges
8.description: Miscellaneous charges not otherwise categorized.

9.title: Transport charges up to a specified location
9.description: Transport charges to be paid by a specified party for a part of a voyage, i.e. up to a specified location.

10.title: Origin port charges
10.description: Charges payable at the port of origin.

11.title: Origin haulage charges
11.description: Haulage charges for the pickup of goods at origin.

12.title: Other charges
12.description: Unspecified charges.

13.title: Specific amount payable
13.description: Amount that the consignor agrees to be invoiced or to pay. This amount is part of the total charges applied to the consignment.

14.title: Transport costs (carriage charges)
14.description: Monetary amount calculated on the basis of the transport tariffs or contract eventually including charges or other costs.

15.title: All costs up to a specified location
15.description: All amounts to be paid by the consignor for a part of the voyage, i.e. up to a location that must be precised. (The remaining part of the voyage to be paid by the consignee) The amounts are calculated by the carrier in accordance with tariffs or in case of special events during the voyage (e.g. rail - freight costs - additional costs).

16.title: Weight/valuation charge
16.description: Code to indicate weight/valuation charges to be either wholly prepaid or wholly collect.

17.title: All costs
17.description: All cost elements.

19.title: Supply of certificate of shipment
19.description: Charges payable for the supply of a certificate of shipment.

20.title: Supply of consular formalities or certificate of origin
20.description: Charges payable for the supply of consular formalities or certificate of origin.

21.title: Supply of non-categorised documentation in paper form
21.description: Charges payable for the supply of one or more documents in paper form that are not otherwise categorised.

22.title: Supply of customs formalities, export
22.description: Charges payable for the supply of export customs formalities.

23.title: Supply of customs formalities, transit
23.description: Charges payable for the supply of transit customs formalities.

24.title: Supply of customs formalities, import
24.description: Charges payable for the supply of import customs formalities.

A.title: Senior person rate
A.description: Rate class applies to senior persons.

B.title: Basic
B.description: Code specifying that the rate or tariff is a basic one.

C.title: Specific commodity rate
C.description: Code specifying the specific commodity rate.

K.title: Rate per kilogram
K.description: Code specifying the rate per kilogram.

M.title: Minimum charge rate
M.description: Code specifying the minimum charge rate.

R.title: Class rate (Reduction on normal rate)
R.description: Code specifying the reduction on normal rate.

S.title: Class rate (Surcharge on normal rate)
S.description: Code specifying the surcharge on normal rate.

1.title: Allowance
1.description: (5044) Allowance expressed as a percentage.

2.title: Charge
2.description: (5044) Charge expressed as a percentage.

3.title: Allowance or charge
3.description: [5044] Allowance or charge expressed as a percentage.

4.title: Reinsurer's share
4.description: To indicate the share of the reinsurer in a treaty.

5.title: Entry percentage
5.description: To indicate the percentage used for the specified entry (e.g. commission %, deposits % ...).

6.title: Quality/yield
6.description: (6318) The percentage of a specified material in the total product.

7.title: Percentage of invoice
7.description: Code specifying the percentage of invoice.

8.title: Reduction/surcharge percentage
8.description: Percentage to calculate a reduction/surcharge.

9.title: Adjustment
9.description: Code specifying the adjustment expressed as a percentage.

10.title: Bureau share
10.description: London insurance market bureau (bureau share in reinsurance treaty).

11.title: Buffer stock requirement
11.description: Anticipated additional consumption to safeguard against unforeseen shortages or demands.

12.title: Discount
12.description: Discount expressed as a percentage.

13.title: Amount tolerance
13.description: Tolerance of amount in percentage.

14.title: Percentage of note
14.description: Percentage of debit or credit note.

15.title: Penalty percentage
15.description: Code specifying the penalty percentage.

16.title: Interest percentage
16.description: Code specifying the interest percentage.

17.title: Part of documentary credit amount
17.description: Part of documentary credit amount in percentage subject to sight payment, deferred payment or acceptance when the documentary credit is available by mixed payment.

18.title: Percentage credit note
18.description: Percentage of a credit note.

19.title: Percentage debit note
19.description: Percentage of a debit note.

20.title: Percentage of insurance
20.description: Code specifying the percentage of insurance.

21.title: Own risk percentage
21.description: Percentage of total amount which is not covered by credit cover.

22.title: Transferred VAT percentage
22.description: VAT percentage rate for which accountability is being transferred from one party to another. VAT means: Value added tax.

23.title: Part time employment
23.description: The time a person is employed expressed as a percentage of the equivalent full time employment.

24.title: Voluntary contribution
24.description: Contribution to a superannuation scheme which is not compulsory, expressed as a percentage of salary.

25.title: Attribute factor
25.description: To indicate a mathematical factor, expressed as a percentage , used to multiply a specified attribute item.

26.title: Additional contribution
26.description: Contribution to a scheme in addition to the normal contribution, expressed as a percentage (in superannuation usually expressed as a percentage of salary).

27.title: Benefits allocation
27.description: Percentage of total benefits allocated to a person.

28.title: Attribute classification
28.description: To indicate the percentage of a specified attribute classification (e.g. percentage contributed before a defined year for superannuation purposes).

29.title: Renegotiation trigger upper limit
29.description: The percentage rise in a currency rate of exchange which would result in renegotiation of prices.

30.title: Renegotiation trigger lower limit
30.description: The percentage fall in a currency rate of exchange which would result in renegotiation of prices.

31.title: Material reduction factor
31.description: The percentage reduction in constituent material which occurs in the production process.

32.title: Acceptable price difference
32.description: The maximum percentage increase or decrease resulting from price recalculation which will not result in price renegotiation.

33.title: Share of buyer's total requirement
33.description: The percentage of the buyer's total acquisition requirement for the referenced or similar item which will be ordered from the named supplier.

34.title: Price increase
34.description: The percentage increase in price of the referenced item since the last notification.

35.title: Share of tool cost paid by buyer
35.description: The percentage of the cost of tooling which will be paid by the buyer.

36.title: Volume capacity usage
36.description: Percentage of the volume capacity used.

37.title: Weight capacity usage
37.description: Percentage of the weight capacity used.

38.title: Loading length capacity usage
38.description: Percentage of the loading length capacity used.

39.title: Share of packaging cost paid by vendor
39.description: The percentage of the cost of packaging which will be paid by the vendor.

40.title: Reduction percentage
40.description: Reduction from an amount/price expressed in a percentage.

41.title: Surcharge percentage
41.description: Additional amount expressed in a percentage.

42.title: Local content
42.description: To indicate the percentage of a products local (i.e. domestic) content.

43.title: Chargeback
43.description: Percentage amount charged back.

44.title: Gross turnover commission
44.description: Percentage of gross turnover used to calculate commission.

45.title: Progress payment percentage
45.description: Indicates the rate applying for a progress payment.

46.title: Offset
46.description: Indicates the figure agreed between parties to calculate an offset.

47.title: Prepaid payment percentage
47.description: A code to indicate the percentage of the prepayment.

48.title: Percentage of work completed
48.description: A code to indicate the percentage of work completed.

1.title: Continental
1.description: The equipment is or will be moving across a continent on an intermodal or multimodal basis.

2.title: Export
2.description: Transport equipment to be exported on a marine vessel.

3.title: Import

4.title: Remain on board
4.description: Transport equipment arriving on a marine vessel is to remain on board.

5.description: Transport equipment is to be shifted from one stowage location on a marine vessel to another on the same vessel.

6.title: Transhipment
6.description: Transport equipment is to be transferred from one marine vessel to another.

7.title: Shortlanded
7.description: Transport equipment notified to arrive which did not arrive on the means of transport.

8.title: Overlanded
8.description: Transport equipment not notified to arrive but which did arrive on the means of transport.

9.title: Domestic
9.description: Transport equipment is used in domestic service.

10.title: Positioning
10.description: Equipment is being transported for positioning purposes.

11.title: Delivery
11.description: Equipment is being delivered.

12.title: Redelivery
12.description: Equipment is being redelivered.

13.title: Repair
13.description: The equipment is for repair.

14.title: Reloader
14.description: Transport equipment to be discharged and subsequently reloaded on the same means of transport but in a different stowage location.

ADR.title: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road (ADR)
ADR.description: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road. ADR is the abbreviation of "Accord europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises dangereuses par route".

ADS.title: NDR European agreement for the transport of dangerous goods on the river Rhine
ADS.description: European agreement giving regulations for the transport of dangerous goods on the river Rhine, officially known as: "Accord europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises dangereuses par navigation sur le Rhin.".

ADT.title: CA, Transport Canada's dangerous goods requirements
ADT.description: Canadian transport of dangerous goods requirements as published by Transport Canada in the Canadian Gazette, Part II.

ADU.title: JP, Japanese maritime safety agency dangerous goods regulation code
ADU.description: Regulation regarding the handling of dangerous goods on vessels issued by Japanese maritime safety agency.

AGS.title: DE, ADR and GGVS combined regulations for combined transport
AGS.description: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au Transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse.

ANR.title: ADNR, Autorisation de transport de matieres Dangereuses pour la Navigation sur le Rhin
ANR.description: Regulations for dangerous goods transportation on the Rhine.

ARD.title: DE, ARD and RID - Combined regulations for combined transport
ARD.description: Combined European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on roads and rails. ARD means: Autorisation de transport par Route de matieres dangereuses. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer.

CFR.title: US, 49 Code of federal regulations
CFR.description: United States federal regulations issued by the US Department of transportation covering the domestic transportation of dangerous goods by truck, rail, water and air.

COM.title: DE, ADR, RID, GGVS and GGVE - Combined regulations for combined transport
COM.description: Combined German and European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads and rails. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuse par Route. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

GVE.title: DE, GGVE (Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn)
GVE.description: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on rail.

GVS.title: DE, GGVS (Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse)
GVS.description: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on road.

ICA.title: IATA ICAO
ICA.description: Regulations covering the international transportation of dangerous goods issued by the International Air Transport Association and the International Civil Aviation Organization.

IMD.title: IMO IMDG code
IMD.description: Regulations regarding the transportation of dangerous goods on ocean-going vessels issued by the International Maritime Organization.

RGE.title: DE, RID and GGVE, Combined regulations for combined transport on rails
RGE.description: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European rails. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

RID.title: Railroad dangerous goods book (RID)
RID.description: International regulations concerning the international carriage of dangerous goods by rail. RID is the abbreviation of "Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer".

UI.title: UK IMO book
UI.description: The United Kingdom (UK) version of the International Maritime Organisation (IMO) book on dangerous goods.

ZZZ.title: Mutually defined
ZZZ.description: Additional and/or other information for the transportation of dangerous goods which are mutually defined.

1.title: Full load
1.description: Container represents the full consignment of goods declared on a single Customs declaration (i.e. all goods in the container relate to a single Customs declaration).

2.title: Part load
2.description: Container represents part of a consignment declared on a single Customs declaration (i.e. the Customs declaration covers more than one container).

3.title: Full load mixed consignments
3.description: Container holds the full consignment related to the Customs declaration but also holds goods related to other declarations.

4.title: Part load mixed consignments
4.description: Container represents part of the consignment declared on a single Customs declaration with the remainder being in other containers. Other goods, related to other declarations, are also in the container.

5.title: Single invoiced load
5.description: Merchandise within a container/package covered by a single invoice.

6.title: Multi invoiced load
6.description: Merchandise within a container/package covered by more than one invoice.

7.title: Empty
7.description: Container holds no goods.

8.title: Full load, multiple bills
8.description: A container representing a consignment of goods for one consignee with multiple bill of lading numbers.

1.title: Transport for the owner's account
1.description: The owner of the transported goods is also the owner of the means of transport or rented it for this transport.

2.title: Transport for another account
2.description: The owner of the transported goods does not own the means of transport or has not rented it for this transport.

3.title: Private transport
3.description: A code indicating privately owned transport.

1.title: Export
1.description: The transport movement is to export the goods from the country.

2.title: Import
2.description: The transport movement is to import the goods into the country.

3.title: Transit
3.description: The cargo is moving in transit through a country and will not become part of the commerce of that country.

4.title: Relay
4.description: The cargo is being moved by more than one transport means in succession under the responsibility of the same carrier.

5.title: Transshipment
5.description: The cargo is being moved by more than one transport means in succession.

1.title: Breakbulk
1.description: Defines the movement of general cargo not carried in ISO standard containers.

2.title: LCL/LCL
2.description: Defines the movement of cargo packed in and unpacked from containers by the carrier on behalf of the shipper/consignee. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load.

3.title: FCL/FCL
3.description: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the shipper or shipper's agent and unpacked by the consignee or consignee's agent. 'FCL' means Full Container Load.

4.title: FCL/LCL
4.description: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the shipper or shipper's agent and unpacked by the carrier. 'FCL' means Full Container Load. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load.

5.title: LCL/FCL
5.description: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the carrier and unpacked by the consignee or consignee's agent. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load. 'FCL' means Full Load.

6.title: Consolidation
6.description: A movement of multiple shipments to a single destination.

7.title: Parcel post
7.description: A movement of material by parcel post.

8.title: Expedited truck
8.description: A movement of material by expedited truck.

9.title: Consignor determined means
9.description: A movement of material by the means determined by the consignor.

10.title: Private parcel service
10.description: A movement of material by a private parcel service.

11.title: House to house
11.description: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked by consignee at final destination.

12.title: House to terminal
12.description: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked at the carrier's inland facility between the ship's point of discharge and the final destination.

13.title: House to pier
13.description: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

14.title: Air charter
14.description: A movement of material by chartered aircraft.

15.title: Air express
15.description: A movement of material by air express service.

16.title: Geographic grouped transport
16.description: A movement of material from multiple origins to a single destination utilizing a single carrier and a single freight bill.

17.title: Less than truck load
17.description: A movement of material on a truck that is not full.

18.title: Pooled piggyback
18.description: A movement of material by a trailer on a railcar.

19.title: Consignee transportation provided
19.description: A movement of material transported by the consignee.

20.title: Rail
20.description: A movement of material to the consignee via rail.

21.title: Terminal to house

22.title: Terminal to terminal
22.description: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and the ship's point of loading and unpacked at a carrier's inland facility between ship's point of discharge and final destination.

23.title: Terminal to pier
23.description: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and ship's point of loading and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

31.title: Pier to house
31.description: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked by consignee at final destination.

32.title: Pier to terminal
32.description: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked at a carrier's inland facility between ship's point of discharge and final destination.

33.title: Pier to pier
33.description: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

41.title: Station to station
41.description: The consignment is moving from one container freight station to another container freight station.

42.title: House to warehouse
42.description: The consignment is moving from the premises of the shipper to a warehouse.

43.title: Warehouse to house
43.description: The consignment is moving from a warehouse to the premises of the consignee.

44.title: Station to house
